==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Teosinte
<hw>Te`o*sin"te</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A large grass (<spn>Euchlaena luxurians</spn>) closely related to
maize. It is native of Mexico and Central America, but is now cultivated
for fodder in the Southern United States and in many warm countries.
Called also <altname>Guatemala grass</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tepal</ent>⟦br⟧
